- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/4/02 4:55:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1010.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TLC bug list.</span><hr size=1> I understand that trying to describe what is &quot;reasonable&quot; is subjective. So let me put it another way. When verant built FV they had rules and a framework laid out that would basically describe the progression of this server. To do this they would need to make some assumptions. This isn't any different than how any business would operate. Some call it forecasting or projections.<br>
<br>
For Verant's premise to work, that is for FV to work, some of these projections would need to materialize. For any EQ server, the most important projection that would need to materialize is the player count. Not just for revenue, but to create and maintain the social and economic dynamic of the server. In FV's case this also has an impact on quests. I am not privy to these forecasts, but I do not believe FV has met its projected player count. I don't think anyone would dispute that. The unexpectedly low population count is making it unreasonably difficult to accomplish a number of quests.<br>
<br>
Now some would argue that, missed projections or not, Verant is not going to change anything because a &quot;handful&quot; of quests have been adversly affected by TLC. They might even be right. But this is a problem that will continue to grow as new expansions and new quests are released. So at what point does Verant need to do something? How many quests have to become &quot;unreasonably difficult&quot; or impossible to do before they take action? <br>
<br>
Now before anyone accuses me of being a power gamer or impatient please consider where I have just come from. I have just spent the last year on the Test server.  When you come from an environment where they can bring down the server at anytime (no notice), wipe gear from you as you zone or worse with NO recourse, well... I think thats about as patient as you can ask a player to be. I didn't whine when they broke all the fear and Feign death spells on test a little while ago. I didn't whine when I zoned into NFP and discovered all my equipment had been wiped. I didn't even whine when I entered my username and password but wound up logging into another persons account. I just pointed out what I thought were problems and thats what I am doing again now.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
